<br>
So what?<br>
<br>
Gandhi (note the position of the &quot;h&quot;, by the way) was pursuing political means - successfully - using a hunger strike as one of many non-violent methods.  He was a great man, unquestionably, but he wasn't a great man <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>because</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> he went on a hunger strike; he was a great man because he had a vision for the people of his country and went to extraordinary lengths to fulfil that vision; all the more extraordinary for being non-violent in nature.<br>
<br>
Blaine is pulling a stunt.  He is a showman, that's what showmen do.  I am not aware of anyone, least of all Blaine, claiming that this is in any way some kind of parallel to Gandhi's hunger strike, or renders him worthy of &quot;respect&quot;.  It is a harmless form of entertainment - well, at least, the only person in any danger from it is Blaine himself.  If it doesn't entertain you, fine; it doesn't much entertain me either.  I am at a total loss as to why some people are getting so upset about it though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ramshutu>ramshutu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bananaman</span><br>  Posts: 1075<br> <font color=#330000>(10/22/03 5:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1077.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.johnsrealmonline.com/classicnick/bananaman/Image33.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good God..</span><hr size=1> I think the idea that moodel was trying to make, is that because this he is not attempting to effect political change, and it's merely being used as a tool for ratings and money, it somewhat belittles, or popularises the idea of a hunger strike. Which in turn cheapens the suffering and pain endured by men and women who have used hunger strikes to change the world for the better.<br>
<br>
Rightly or wrongly, I think that is the point he was trying to make. <p><br>
